Class WaveletFetchedEvent

java.lang.Object
  com.google.wave.api.event.AbstractEvent
      com.google.wave.api.event.WaveletFetchedEvent
All Implemented Interfaces:
Event
public class WaveletFetchedEvent
extends AbstractEvent

Event triggered when a wavelet is fetched. This event is triggered after a robot requests to see another wavelet. The robot has to be a participant of the requested wavelet.

bundle - the message bundle this event belongs to.
modifiedBy - the id of the participant that triggered this event.
timestamp - the timestamp of this event.
message - the message that was passed into the wavelet fetch operation.
rootBlipId - the root blip id of the wavelet where this event occurs.
waveletData - the wavelet data of the fetched wavelet.
blips - the blips of the fetched wavelet.
